short.am,ar,bg,bn,ca,cs,da,de,el,en,en_AU,en_G: Add keyboard shortcuts for moving tabs between windows

long.am,ar,bg,bn,ca,cs,da,de,el,en,en_AU,en_G:
This extension adds keyboard shortcuts for moving tabs between Chrome Windows. The main target audience is developers who want to avoid using the mouse to navigate Chrome.

Here are the supported actions:

  * Move tabs to next window (or into new window if only one window exists), 
  * Move tabs left,
  * Move tabs right,
  * Undock tabs to new window,
  * Undock tab to popup window (without tabs or address bar), and 
  * Toggle the pinned state of a tab

Note that most of these commands support operating on multiple tabs.  You can select multiple tabs by holding down Ctrl/Cmd or Shift while clicking on tabs.

To update the keyboard shortcut bindings, visit chrome://extensions/shortcuts
